HIGH
FREQUENCY
DIFFRACTION
BY
A
WEDGE
WITH
A
LINEARLY
VARYING
SURFACE
IMPEDANCE
AN
ASYMPTOTIC
REPRESENTATION
VALID
BOTH
IN
THE
ILLUMINATED
AND
SHADOW
REGIONS
IS
DERIVED
FOR
THE
SCATTERED
FIELD
DUE
TO
AN
INCIDENT
PLANE
WAVE
AND
ITS
PROPERTIES
ARE
ANALYSED
AS
A
FUNCTION
OF
THE
RATE
OF
VARIATION
OF
SURFACE
IMPEDANCE
